replies.body:
Riot Sparkle, since you have paid some attention to this and some bugs. currently I am having an issue where I go in and edit a rune page. but if for some reason I either made an error on selecting, or say the time ran out and it just closes the rune page and sets it back to default, I can no longer use the inner keys in my game for any abilities, attack move, flash, ward, or back yet I can use tab to see the score board escape to leave game. some times when I leave game, exit league, and log back in I get back to normal, but it is not 100 percent. to prove that it is not my personal lap top keyboard I bought an external gaming keyboard, and I come across the same issue. 

I have submitted a ticket on this issue, and was told to delete input.ini setting and persisted settings. Reinstall league, and my favorite was run as administrator. while in game doing all three of these things take time and will ruin the game for the people I am playing with as I normally queue as mid, but that is neither here nor there. 

I have done my own bug testing, the problem with the incomplete ruin page seems to be the main way I can recreate this issue. Have you ever heard of this before? also the only program that is in the background is Skype, not discord. any ideas?{{sticker:cass-cry}}

Whenever im changing my rune pages it always resets to the previous page when I save it

Like if i change a precision/sorcery page to inspiration/domination, once i press save it reverts back to the precision/sorcery page and its like wtf

{{sticker:sg-zephyr}}
